{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "kjva:job.16",
    "translationId": "kjva",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 16,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 16",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 16 in King James Version with Apocrypha."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.1",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:1",
      "text": "Then Job answered and said,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.2",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:2",
      "text": "I have heard many such things: miserable comforters are ye all.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.3",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:3",
      "text": "Shall vain words have an end? or what emboldeneth thee that thou answerest?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.4",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:4",
      "text": "I also could speak as ye do: if your soul were in my soul’s stead, I could heap up words against you, and shake mine head at you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.5",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:5",
      "text": "But I would strengthen you with my mouth, and the moving of my lips should asswage your grief.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.6",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:6",
      "text": "Though I speak, my grief is not asswaged: and though I forbear, what am I eased?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.7",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:7",
      "text": "But now he hath made me weary: thou hast made desolate all my company.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.8",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:8",
      "text": "And thou hast filled me with wrinkles, which is a witness against me: and my leanness rising up in me beareth witness to my face.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.9",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:9",
      "text": "He teareth me in his wrath, who hateth me: he gnasheth upon me with his teeth; mine enemy sharpeneth his eyes upon me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.10",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:10",
      "text": "They have gaped upon me with their mouth; they have smitten me upon the cheek reproachfully; they have gathered themselves together against me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.11",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:11",
      "text": "God hath delivered me to the ungodly, and turned me over into the hands of the wicked.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.12",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:12",
      "text": "I was at ease, but he hath broken me asunder: he hath also taken me by my neck, and shaken me to pieces, and set me up for his mark.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.13",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:13",
      "text": "His archers compass me round about, he cleaveth my reins asunder, and doth not spare; he poureth out my gall upon the ground.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.14",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:14",
      "text": "He breaketh me with breach upon breach, he runneth upon me like a giant.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.15",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:15",
      "text": "I have sewed sackcloth upon my skin, and defiled my horn in the dust.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.16",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:16",
      "text": "My face is foul with weeping, and on my eyelids is the shadow of death;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.17",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:17",
      "text": "Not for any injustice in mine hands: also my prayer is pure.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.18",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:18",
      "text": "O earth, cover not thou my blood, and let my cry have no place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.19",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:19",
      "text": "Also now, behold, my witness is in heaven, and my record is on high.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.20",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:20",
      "text": "My friends scorn me: but mine eye poureth out tears unto God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.21",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:21",
      "text": "O that one might plead for a man with God, as a man pleadeth for his neighbour!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "kjva:job.16.22",
      "translationId": "kjva",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 16,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 16:22",
      "text": "When a few years are come, then I shall go the way whence I shall not return.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
